Title : Westminster Bank, London
Text : [[File:15 Bishopsgate (geograph 2541490).jpg|thumb|Exterior]]
{{Commons category|15 Bishopsgate, London}}
'''Westminster Bank''' is a [[Grade I listed building]] in the [[City of London]].<ref name="EngHet">{{National Heritage List for England |num=1191569 |desc=Westminster Bank |access-date=9 July 2015}}</ref> The building is now known as '''Gibson Hall''', after the name of its designer, [[John Gibson (architect)|John Gibson]].

Built in 1865, was commissioned as a new head office for the directors of the National Provincial Bank of England in Bishopsgate.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.theperfectweddingcompany.org/wedding-blogger/gibson-hall-wedding-venue/|title=Gibson Hall Wedding Venue|last=|first=|date=|website=The Perfect Wedding Company|publisher=|access-date=}}</ref>

Gibson Hall's exterior elevation features curved panels picturing the crafts and industries that the bank supplied its financial services to. The Building was listed as a Grade I building in 1950.

Since its name was changed to Gibson Hall in 1990s, the hall has been operating solely as an events hosting venue available for hire to the public.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.gibsonhall.com/history|title=Gibson Hall History|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=|access-date=}}</ref>

